# Data Model Sync Rule

When a feature changes the **persisted data model** (localStorage keys or the shape/fields of any stored object), the app-wide ERD at `.specify/memory/app-data-model.md` must be updated.

## When to trigger

- A new field is added to an entity stored in localStorage (e.g. adding `schedule` to disciplines).
- An existing field's type, validation range, or semantics change (e.g. points range 1–50 → 1–500).
- A new localStorage key is introduced or an existing one is removed.
- A feature's `data-model.md` documents schema changes.

## What to do

After the feature's `data-model.md` is written or updated, run:

```
/speckit.sync-data-model
```

This merges the feature's changes into the global ERD and appends a change log entry.

## ERD location

`.specify/memory/app-data-model.md`
